                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <head>No. 208.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hardinge</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 10, 1886</date>. [Received August
                        11.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of yesterday, drawing the attention of Her Majesty’s Government to the
                    alleged unwarrantable and unfriendly treatment experienced by the American
                    fishing schooner Battler, on the 3d instant, upon the occasion of her being
                    driven by stress of weather to find shelter in the harbor of Shelburne, Nova
                    Scotia.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES HARDINGE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
